GNP urged to stop begging for U.S. Forces' continued presence 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 27 (KCNA) -- The Solidarity for Implementing the South-North Joint Declaration reportedly issued on Feb. 22 a statement titled "The Grand National Party begging for the U.S. Forces' continued presence in South Korea should cease to exist".
 The statement accused the GNP of imploring for the continued presence of the U.S. Forces, murderers, in South Korea and talking about the "alliance" between South Korea and the U.S. at a time when all the South Koreans are trembling with bitter hatred for GIs' unabated crimes and the U.S. moves to launch a nuclear war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Explaining the reason why the GNP is so eagerly begging the U.S. Forces to remain in South Korea, the statement said that it is doing so because the changed times and the growing desire for national reconciliation have deprived its "protectors" of any justification to remain on this land any longer. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement said the solidarity will carry on its fierce struggle until the GNP is thrown overboard if it persists in its acts of treachery and anachronistic acts.

Seminars held in different countries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 27 (KCNA) -- Seminars on Kim Jong Il's idea and theory and army-based leadership exploits were held in Uganda, Nepal, Tanzania, Bulgaria, Ukraine, France, Portugal, Tajikistan from February 6 to 15 on the occasion of his birthday (February 16).
 Speakers at the seminars said that the Juche idea has been overall developed in depth by Kim Jong Il's energetic ideological  and theoretical activities, so that it has become a foundation of policies of the DPRK party and state and a powerful ideological instrument for leading the cause of global independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His army-based policy is representing the principle and requirement of the Juche idea, they said, stressing that the army-based policy will be glorified forever as the most correct political mode because it is based on the Juche idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Saying that one of the U.S. purposes to stifle the DPRK through a nuclear racket is to prevent the DPRK army-based policy from influencing the world, they called for supporting and defending his army-based policy together with the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people, single-heartedly united around their leader and guided by the Juche idea, will achieve national reunification and build a powerful socialist nation, foiling all challenges and obstructive moves of the imperialists, they stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A congratulatory message and letter to Kim Jong Il were adopted at seminars in Ukraine and Kathmandu, Nepal.

DPRK vows to implement declaration of Copenhagen Summit on Social Development 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 27 (KCNA) -- The DPRK Government will continue enforcing the advantageous social policies in the interests of the people and consolidating and developing them and promote the exchange of experience and effective  cooperation with the international bodies and other countries and thus sincerely implement the target of the declaration adopted at the un new millennium summit and the declaration of the Copenhagen Summit Meeting on Social Development.
 The DPRK delegate said this, addressing the 41st meeting of the un social development committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Each government plays a decisive role in achieving social development. The experience of the DPRK proves that the government's political will related to the field of social development and the people's viewpoint on it and the policy on social development and its implementation are essential for this development. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK has been able to invariably enforce social policies for the people even under the difficult economic conditions caused by the pressure and blockade of outside forces in recent years because it has shown constant state concern for the social wellbeing of the people and exerted positive efforts  for it, regarding President Kim Il Sung's idea "believing in the people as in heaven" as a basic principle of the government policy and activity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He underscored the importance of encouraging each government to work out a strategy for social development and increase its efforts for it and realize international cooperation in order to preserve and step up the social policies and smoothly carry out them.

More U.S. aerial espionage committed against DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 27 (KCNA) -- The U.S. imperialist warhawks again let their strategic reconnaissance plane illegally intrude into the territorial air of the DPRK to spy on it on Feb. 26.
 RC-135 strategic reconnaissance plane that took off an overseas base made shuttle-flights in the air above the territorial waters in the East Sea of the DPRK between Musudan and Hodo peninsula for hours from about 8:25 on an espionage mission. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This U.S. intrusion and espionage committed against the DPRK in the wake of its similar crime perpetrated on Feb. 24 are a wanton infringement on the sovereignty of the DPRK and a grave violation of international law as they are part of the U.S. imperialist warmongers' vicious moves to stifle the DPRK by force of arms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The revolutionary armed forces of the DPRK warn that they would take a decisive self-defensive step against the intruders and provocateurs.

Sports masters increase in Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 27 (KCNA) --The number of masters of sports has rapidly increased in Korea in recent years.
 In Juche 45 (1956) there were only thirteen masters of sports in the country. But now the number has reached some 3,250. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Over the past eight years 1,280 athletes have won the degree of sports master. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The rapid increase in the number of sports masters is attributable to ever growing state and public concern for the sports development. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The " regulations on degree of master of sports" was enacted in the country on January 15, 1955 for the purpose of promoting the rapid sports development of the country, properly estimating athletes' talents and achievements and encouraging them to bring their political and ideological, physical and technical preparedness into full play. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 According to the regulations, those who distinguish themselves in sports activities are awarded  the degree of sports master, as well as the titles of people's sportspersons and merited sport persons.

Candlelight demonstration in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 27 (KCNA) -- The All-People Measure Committee for Sin Hyo Sun and Sim Mi Son, schoolgirls killed by a U.S. armored car reportedly held the 89th-day candlelight demonstration at Kwanghwamun in Seoul on Feb. 22.
 The demonstration continued more than 1 hour. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The demonstrators vowed to steadfastly continue the anti-U.S. candlelight march in the future. Han Sang Ryol, permanent representative of the committee, shouted slogans "long live national cooperation", "Long live national independence," "Long live the grand candlelight march". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the demonstration, the committee declared a week of national independence, peace against war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The committee announced that it would hold a function for the day of action of people from all walks of life from Feb. 24 to 28 and stage a grand candlelight march on March 1. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, anti-U.S., anti-war demonstrations were held in different parts of Seoul to oppose the Iraqi war by the U.S.

Implementation of June 15 North-South Joint Declaration called for
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 27 (KCNA) -- The historic June 15 North-South Joint Declaration, a declaration for national independence and the great unity of the Korean nation, provides  a sure guarantee for tiding over the prevailing grave situation, defending the sovereignty of the country and the security of the nation and promoting the process of reconciliation and reunification, says Rodong Sinmun today in a signed article.
 The spirit of national independence is the kernel of the joint declaration, it says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Unity is a source of strength and guarantees victory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean nation has already grasped this truth in the course of the nationwide reunification movement to achieve the independent and peaceful reunification of the country in the idea of "By Our Nation Itself." No ferocious aggressor will dare to hurt the Korean nation when all the Koreans in the north, south and overseas put the common interests of the nation above all and subordinate everything to it and unite as close as one in the spirit of national independence and patriotism. 
 The compatriots from all walks of life in the north, south and overseas should bravely take the road of patriotism to preserve and implement the June 15 Joint Declaration with the transparent spirit of the nation and patriotic will to bring earlier the  independent and peaceful reunification of the country by the concerted efforts of the nation no matter how the situation and atmosphere may change and no matter what others may say. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Differing political view, religious belief, class and social strata can in no way be a stumbling block on the road of patriotism to defend the peace of the country and the security of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The fellow countrymen should face up to the present situation where the destiny of the nation is now exposed to a serious threat and take the road of national unity without hesitation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. arrogant and provocative attempt to launch a war of aggression against the DPRK is bound to go busted when all the Koreans in the north, south and overseas struggle in unity under the uplifted banner of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration.
